      "date": "2014-01-31 20:56:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/aaab0a30-8aaf-11e3-be08-52540035b04c).  Ran 19 tests.  2 tests failed: sanity-hsm, sanityn.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1f2400a3b846ec3809a6da986c3672c904855710",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-02-05 17:59:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI am not fan of adding extra flag here, since it might always cause some compatible problem here.\n\nJust curious, why do we need client to tell server the object needs to be local? I think server should return EREMOTE in this case anyway, and client should handle it by different cases?  But I might miss sth here. could you please explain advantages here? Thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "61d215f4728925af25c0cd52b88a730ca0de443a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2014-02-05 18:23:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(6 comments)\n\nI don't think this makes sense, please clarify why you think we need this flag and what is expected behavior and use cases. Maybe I misunderstood the idea.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "588b0ec87a6dfb473d7d1267d242bc95debca51f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-02-05 20:18:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'll try to rework this so that it just strengthens the semantics of HABEO_CORPUS.\n\n> I am not fan of adding extra flag here, since it might always cause some compatible problem here.\n\nSeveral handlers require the fid1 object to exist and be local (several assert on this). So adding a flag that causes then to return -EPROTO rather than crash should not be a compatibility issue.\n\n> Just curious, why do we need client to tell server the object needs to be local?\n\nI don't understand.\n\n> I don't think this makes sense, please clarify why you think we need this flag and what is expected behavior and use cases. Maybe I misunderstood the idea.\n\nThe idea was to reject requests sent to the wrong MDT (or with a bad object) early and cleanly rather than crashing because of some failed assertion in lu_object_attr() or somewhere...\n\nIt wasn't obvious to me how to fix HABEO_CORPUS in this way. Since the mdt and ost unpacking functions have different expectations about setting tsi_corpus.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ba3ae8c9f5fe3f44859d4590817d76e8354cfd41",
